result.name: Lazy Creatures

reviews.text:
Random search in Kowloon City, turned out it was a surprise! 

Environment: 5/5
Coffee: 4/5
Services: 5/5
Food: NA
Price: 4/5

- The environment is very cozy with a small corner that you can sit on the floor with no shoes on.
- The coffee is pretty good, I have high standard on coffee and I give it a 4/5 for the portion I have for the price and the taste.
- Services is extremely good, I ordered a croissant and when I ordered a coffee, I told them I cannot have milk. They told me that the croissant is heavy with butter and asked whether I can have it. They gave me a full refund after I said I cannot. Very considerate customer service.

I like this neighborhood gem. Will go again when I want some coffee or down time :)
Very good place to bring dogs to chill and relax and nice coffee.

This has quickly become my favorite cafe in the neighborhood.  They are located on a very charming corner of a rounded lot on the ground floor of an old yet welcoming building in Kowloon City.  The location is an oasis of sorts, even though it is surrounded by transit-something about this spot captures your attention and diminishes the background traffic noises.  The periphery of the lot offers some of the widest pedestrian space in Hong Kong.  

They have a nice simple menu and take great care in the preparation of their drinks.  Non-diary options are available for those looking to avoid milk in their beverages.  The spot has become a bit of a hub for those with pets and on weekends you can count on being surrounded by dogs and cats of all temperaments.  It’s all very relaxed and a nice change of pace for the busy Hong Kong life.

Cute little cafe in an unassuming location with outdoors seating. They have oat milk for those who are non dairy friendly. The two gentlemen baristas were super friendly. Furry friends are welcomed. A nice place to just be lazy and enjoy some caffeine.

a quiet and cozy place to have a coffee or a light snack, the menu contains a few tasty elements and the pies, sausage and open topped sandwiches are all delicious. Customers with pets are allowed to sit at the front of the shop and they have dog treats and places to secure your pet if they are leashed.
